01:37:36,977 --> 01:37:37,944
l'm not selling

955
01:37:39,479 --> 01:37:42,778
But madam, we had a deal...
- Why are you late ?

956
01:37:43,316 --> 01:37:43,941
But ma'am...

957
01:37:44,150 --> 01:37:44,775
Shut up !

958
01:37:45,485 --> 01:37:47,783
So you can't sell the Taj Mahal to me ?

959
01:37:50,323 --> 01:37:51,790
lt's all a big mistake

960
01:37:52,993 --> 01:37:54,961
And you have wasted my time

961
01:37:56,896 --> 01:37:57,794
One minute

962
01:38:01,835 --> 01:38:08,468
l said l can't sell the Taj Mahal
but it doesn't mean you can't have it

963
01:38:09,175 --> 01:38:10,301
l don't understand

964
01:38:13,680 --> 01:38:16,342
You can lease it on rent

965
01:38:19,686 --> 01:38:20,311
For how long ?

966
01:38:21,521 --> 01:38:22,818
Five years

967
01:38:24,190 --> 01:38:24,849
Ten

968
01:38:25,025 --> 01:38:25,821
Ten ?

969
01:38:28,028 --> 01:38:32,158
Lease document ready for five.
interested, not interested ?

970
01:38:32,866 --> 01:38:33,833
lnterested, interested

971
01:38:47,047 --> 01:38:49,675
Why are you protesting ?
- Because we have grievances

972
01:38:49,883 --> 01:38:53,341
What grievances ?
- Meet our demands or else

973
01:38:54,387 --> 01:38:55,046
What demands ?

974
01:38:56,556 --> 01:38:58,683
The revolution...
- Long live the revolution

975
01:38:58,892 --> 01:39:01,019
Never mind that,
but what are your demands ?

976
01:39:01,728 --> 01:39:03,025
Down with tyranny

977
01:39:03,229 --> 01:39:04,196
Whose...?
- Every tyrant's

978
01:39:04,397 --> 01:39:05,364
Five years

979
01:39:06,900 --> 01:39:07,867
All Harry Epstein's

980
01:39:10,070 --> 01:39:14,530
For a price of 250 million dollars.
- Good doing business with you

981
01:39:19,746 --> 01:39:26,709
And here is your fee
5 million Rupees, cash

982
01:39:26,986 --> 01:39:29,546
Tell me your demands.
- Quit lndia

983
01:39:29,756 --> 01:39:31,223
Quit lndia, quit lndia

984
01:39:31,591 --> 01:39:35,220
Quit lndia...?
- State your demands or l'll arrest you

985
01:39:35,795 --> 01:39:39,731
We demand that Ms Kalasakhi...
- But l'm Phoolsakhi !

986
01:39:39,999 --> 01:39:42,900
Tell them !
- You've got the address wrong

987
01:39:43,103 --> 01:39:50,737
She is Ms Phoolsakhi. Now get out.
- Okay. Sorry. Fine. Relax. Don't mind

988
01:39:55,448 --> 01:39:57,245
Okay then, goodbye.
- Thank you madam

989
01:39:57,484 --> 01:39:58,917
See you.
- Namaste

990
01:39:59,119 --> 01:40:01,587
Which country are you from ?
- Oh, all of them

991
01:40:03,123 --> 01:40:04,249
Your guests should be here soon

992
01:40:06,126 --> 01:40:07,252
Goodbye

993
01:40:09,963 --> 01:40:12,090
What happened to this elevator ?
- Could be stuck somewhere

994
01:40:15,034 --> 01:40:20,301
lt's coming.
- Let's go

995
01:40:31,151 --> 01:40:34,450
Finished ?
- Nearly

996
01:41:04,517 --> 01:41:07,486
lt sure is nice of Mr Bunty to throw us
this wonderful wedding party

997
01:41:07,687 --> 01:41:11,987
And you ! Thank you,
it's a dream come true

998
01:41:17,864 --> 01:41:18,990
Not possible

999
01:41:19,532 --> 01:41:22,990
What do you mean not-possible,
l own the Taj Mahal

1000
01:41:23,369 --> 01:41:26,497
ls he nuts ?
He says he owns the Taj Mahal !

1001
01:41:26,873 --> 01:41:29,171
Poor thing,
God can really be cruel sometimes

1002
01:41:29,909 --> 01:41:34,846
Open the gate before l fire you
... dismiss you

1003
01:41:35,048 --> 01:41:37,676
Dismiss ?
He says he'll get us dismissed

1004
01:41:37,884 --> 01:41:41,183
Doctor ? You need one ?
We call doctor ?

1005
01:41:41,387 --> 01:41:44,515
No doctor ! You talk to Mr Bunty

1006
01:41:45,558 --> 01:41:47,025
He wants some Bunty fellow

1007
01:41:48,061 --> 01:41:50,359
What Bunty...? Hey wait a minute
are they Bunty and Babli ?

1008
01:42:24,898 --> 01:42:26,092
So finally you arrive !

1009
01:42:27,100 --> 01:42:29,728
They sold the Taj and scooted while
you stood by and watched it happen ?

1010
01:42:30,770 --> 01:42:33,898
Tomorrow when you sell it again
l'll still be left watching

1011
01:42:34,107 --> 01:42:36,234
What !
- Look madam...

1012
01:42:38,444 --> 01:42:41,242
a bull doesn't budge
until he sees red in his face...

1013
01:42:41,447 --> 01:42:43,244
and it takes a scam to prod me into
action. l just got the news, no ?

1014
01:42:43,449 --> 01:42:46,077
That's no way to talk.
- Really ? And how did they talk ?

1015
01:42:46,619 --> 01:42:51,249
Go on, file your report about
descriptions, characteristics

1016
01:42:52,458 --> 01:42:53,925
Stop staring at me and do it

1017
01:42:59,632 --> 01:43:03,432
No one could've pulled off this caper
without the help of insiders

1018
01:43:03,636 --> 01:43:05,763
Who could it be ?
- Could've been you, madam

1019
01:43:07,140 --> 01:43:08,767
You left her alone in the room
at a perfect time

1020
01:43:09,976 --> 01:43:17,940
Corruption happens at the top floor.
But one has to climb from the ground floor

1021
01:43:20,987 --> 01:43:28,450
There's a saying amongst us policemen.
Orderlies make more under the table

1022
01:43:32,999 --> 01:43:33,624
See son...

1023
01:43:35,501 --> 01:43:41,963
you shouldn't have gone to the wedding,
that too in a new car. Getting it ?

1024
01:43:51,250 --> 01:43:51,978
Hey trumpet

1025
01:43:53,720 --> 01:43:54,482
Yes sir ?

1026
01:43:55,021 --> 01:43:56,147
What's the most requested
song nowadays ?

1027
01:43:58,458 --> 01:44:02,485
Babu'ji, slow it down now

1028
01:44:03,863 --> 01:44:04,830
Stand up here

1029
01:44:07,700 --> 01:44:08,325
Play

1030
01:44:19,212 --> 01:44:21,180
l heard you took an American
to his wedding altar

1031
01:44:26,219 --> 01:44:28,187
No, sir

1032
01:44:28,421 --> 01:44:32,858
l know their names.
l want to know where they are

1033
01:44:40,066 --> 01:44:44,025
Harry says, he was so smooth,
and convincing. Harry's no fool

1034
01:44:44,737 --> 01:44:46,364
And you believed ?
- l did

1035
01:44:46,572 --> 01:44:50,201
lt was in the Times of lndia.
- All newspapers say...

1036
01:44:50,410 --> 01:44:52,807
all Americans have sex all the day,
l believe ?

1037
01:44:54,580 --> 01:44:59,210
Don't look at it, you hear me ?
Don't look at it

1038
01:44:59,452 --> 01:45:02,546
Sir how about leaving ?
What can we possibly get to know here ?

1039
01:45:02,755 --> 01:45:06,885
Here you learn
to what lengths a man can go...

1040
01:45:07,093 --> 01:45:07,718
for the smallest of things

1041
01:45:09,262 --> 01:45:13,221
Get the serial numbers of the currency
that he withdrew from his bank

1042
01:45:14,267 --> 01:45:16,064
Tell me joke

1043
01:45:16,769 --> 01:45:17,565
Non-veg

1044
01:45:31,150 --> 01:45:34,916
Tired of turning wheels ? Now watch
how the wheels of fortune turn

1045
01:45:36,122 --> 01:45:41,082
l didn't see a thing. What can l say?
l'm a simple honest man

1046
01:45:41,461 --> 01:45:46,421
God ! This one turns out to be honest!
Wheel back that car...

1047
01:45:47,800 --> 01:45:49,097
go on... back out...

1048
01:45:49,635 --> 01:45:54,595
go away, far away

1049
01:45:55,308 --> 01:45:56,935
There. Stop

1050
01:45:57,643 --> 01:46:00,942
The longer the distance,
the more it looks like an accident

1051
01:46:01,180 --> 01:46:05,947
Don't move or l'll shoot.
- Sir, what are you saying ?

1052
01:46:06,185 --> 01:46:09,621
l told you ! l saw nothing.
- No one's ever seen...

1053
01:46:09,822 --> 01:46:11,619
what's about to happen right now

1054
01:46:12,725 --> 01:46:15,125
Come on, slam the car.
- No... please

1055
01:46:15,328 --> 01:46:17,796
Slam him.
- Please ! No...

1056
01:46:19,532 --> 01:46:20,123
l saw, l saw! l saw everything

1057
01:46:20,333 --> 01:46:21,459
Turn off the engine

1058
01:46:22,001 --> 01:46:23,298
Stand straight

1059
01:46:25,905 --> 01:46:32,555
See no evil. Speak no evil. Hear no evil
but if you can profit, grab it

1060
01:46:33,179 --> 01:46:36,637
Gandhi'ji would've come here personally
to whack you for being so honest

1061
01:46:37,350 --> 01:46:41,480
Who else was in it with them?
Go on, give him every detail

1062
01:46:42,922 --> 01:46:46,323
What's wrong ? Why are you sulking?
You're upset with me ?

1063
01:46:46,592 --> 01:46:51,996
Moron, the Taj got sold, not your taxi.
Like some nuts ? No ? Suit yourself

1064
01:46:52,198 --> 01:46:56,328
There was no corner of the country
Bunty and Babli hadn't been to

1065
01:46:56,536 --> 01:47:00,495
And every newspaper
was cheering their ingenuity

1066
01:47:00,740 --> 01:47:04,335
But l was dying to see them
behind bars

1067
01:47:04,336 --> 01:47:07,002
6 MONTH LATER

1068
01:47:07,580 --> 01:47:10,845
No there's no mistake about this order.
Your assignment is being changed

1069
01:47:11,050 --> 01:47:14,850
But l've completely
committed myself to the case

1070
01:47:15,721 --> 01:47:18,019
Bunty-Babli's case is being assigned
to the federal agencies

1071
01:47:18,224 --> 01:47:20,021
To whom ?
- Federal investigation

1072
01:47:20,226 --> 01:47:21,352
God !

1073
01:47:22,728 --> 01:47:27,028
Our politicians have become honest?
The feds have time for Bunty and Babli ?

1074
01:47:27,233 --> 01:47:30,031
They have your sympathies?
- Not those two

1075
01:47:30,236 --> 01:47:34,696
My sympathies are with the feds.
- You think the feds can't get them ?

1076
01:47:35,808 --> 01:47:38,868
Why ?
- Because they can't think like them

1077
01:47:39,078 --> 01:47:40,875
And you can?

1078
01:47:41,080 --> 01:47:43,878
l'm beginning to feel
we're related somehow

1079
01:47:47,587 --> 01:47:51,045
From tomorrow, you're taking charge
of the gold at the airport

1080
01:47:56,629 --> 01:47:57,561
Very well sir

1081
01:47:58,631 --> 01:47:59,893
You're the boss

1082
01:48:01,300 --> 01:48:03,393
l'll take charge of hell
if you want me to

1083
01:48:04,103 --> 01:48:06,571
Anyway what's the score?
- What ?

1084
01:48:07,940 --> 01:48:11,398
l found myself a night-watchman's job.
This is how l got to bide my time

1085
01:48:12,645 --> 01:48:13,236
Dashrath Singh...

1086
01:48:16,515 --> 01:48:19,916
lf there's anybody who'll lay a finger
on Bunty and Babli, it's me

1087
01:48:33,132 --> 01:48:36,431
You find this funny ?
You can do this yourself the next time

1088
01:48:36,636 --> 01:48:39,104
l won't be able to do this
even if l tried, love

1089
01:48:40,306 --> 01:48:42,433
But you can make a mockery of
those who do ?

1090
01:48:43,142 --> 01:48:48,603
Ok, l'm sorry
- What idiot could've made you a father

1091
01:48:50,149 --> 01:48:51,116
You

1092
01:48:55,488 --> 01:48:58,457
One rum, large

1093
01:48:59,158 --> 01:49:01,126
You don't need to pay sir

1094
01:49:01,360 --> 01:49:03,794
Did l mention l'm a policeman?
- Hear me out, sir

1095
01:49:04,030 --> 01:49:08,626
The gentleman out there is hosting
food and drinks for all guests tonight

1096
01:49:08,834 --> 01:49:11,302
Who...?
- The man in black

1097
01:49:12,505 --> 01:49:14,302
They're buying this restaurant

1098
01:49:14,507 --> 01:49:18,307
No way. We're picking up the tab
for everyone tonight

1099
01:49:18,511 --> 01:49:21,139
Not tonight. Tomorrow

1100
01:49:21,514 --> 01:49:28,317
From tomorrow, this hotel is yours
to do as you please. But tonight's on me

1101
01:49:28,688 --> 01:49:35,992
Friends, cocktails and dinner
for everyone on the house

1102
01:49:39,198 --> 01:49:39,823
Vodka

1103
01:49:44,603 --> 01:49:45,262
Whiskey

1104
01:49:47,039 --> 01:49:47,664
Cocktail?

1105
01:49:49,542 --> 01:49:50,201
Gin

1106
01:49:55,047 --> 01:49:56,014
Rum

1107
01:49:58,551 --> 01:50:03,181
Flying to the moon?
- You're selling the tickets ?

1108
01:50:04,223 --> 01:50:06,691
You've just bought yourself
a one-way ticket

1109
01:50:08,227 --> 01:50:14,860
l don't believe much in buying tickets
but yes, l do want to fly to the moon

1110
01:50:15,234 --> 01:50:16,861
You're a man in a hurry?

1111
01:50:18,904 --> 01:50:19,871
Somewhat

1112
01:50:21,907 --> 01:50:24,535
There's this one place in which
men-in-a-hurry usually end up

1113
01:50:31,083 --> 01:50:32,550
You see...
- What ?

1114
01:50:33,452 --> 01:50:38,219
This world we live in
has two kinds of people

1115
01:50:38,424 --> 01:50:41,723
l see.
- One, the kind that listens

1116
01:50:41,994 --> 01:50:48,058
And the kind that talks.
l belong to the latter

1117
01:50:50,803 --> 01:50:55,740
So sure of yourself ? What do you do?
- Cleaning

1118
01:50:57,943 --> 01:51:02,403
l'm in the cleaning business.
We clean out places

1119
01:51:02,782 --> 01:51:05,250
What kind of places ?
- Any kind

1120
01:51:07,119 --> 01:51:12,250
So you like tidy places?
- No, l like tidy sums of money

1121
01:51:15,294 --> 01:51:19,253
lnteresting man.
Where are you from?
- Allahabad

1122
01:51:19,498 --> 01:51:22,592
Aha, you look that type

1123
01:51:23,836 --> 01:51:25,428
Sir, one more large ?

1124
01:51:26,472 --> 01:51:27,598
Bring it on then

1125
01:51:30,810 --> 01:51:32,141
What's happening here ?

1126
01:51:32,645 --> 01:51:36,445
You're smoking in front of your baby?
- How the hell can he see me ?

1127
01:51:36,649 --> 01:51:39,117
Babies know everything.
- How can they know everything ?

1128
01:51:39,318 --> 01:51:39,909
Stop it !

1129
01:51:41,320 --> 01:51:45,780
l get the feeling l'm her baby

1130
01:51:46,492 --> 01:51:47,789
And he who is he ?

1131
01:51:48,060 --> 01:51:49,618
l... am...
- He is...

1132
01:51:49,829 --> 01:51:51,456
Whoever, doesn't matter. Come on

1133
01:51:52,198 --> 01:51:55,292
Women... are like this only.
- How and how do you think women are ?

1134
01:51:56,502 --> 01:52:00,302
Oye, don't stoke my anger.
- Hello, what's happening here ?

1135
01:52:01,173 --> 01:52:04,973
A fight can't you see?
- That l can, but why ?

1136
01:52:05,177 --> 01:52:09,807
Private matters of husband-wife!
How meddlesome !

1137
01:52:10,349 --> 01:52:11,475
Please stub that out

1138
01:52:12,351 --> 01:52:15,149
You look like a long lost father!
Ought to be setting an example for him

1139
01:52:16,088 --> 01:52:19,319
And you better come along.
l'm checking out the rooms in this hotel

1140
01:52:20,860 --> 01:52:21,986
Don't take too long

1141
01:52:26,565 --> 01:52:30,001
Don't come back in an hour or two.
Spoilt the mood for no rhyme or reason

1142
01:52:30,536 --> 01:52:32,663
You seem to be much fallen-in-love

1143
01:52:36,542 --> 01:52:40,501
You've never fallen... in love?

1144
01:52:45,050 --> 01:52:47,018
Once, a little

1145
01:52:48,554 --> 01:52:49,680
What?

1146
01:52:51,056 --> 01:52:52,182
A little

1147
01:52:57,396 --> 01:53:02,857
ln a summer of Delhi
l came upon her

1148
01:53:04,069 --> 01:53:07,869
Every single day on bus number 481 ...

1149
01:53:08,541 --> 01:53:11,203
l would fall all over myself
to vacate the ladies' seat...

1150
01:53:11,410 --> 01:53:14,208
and she would sit down
with the sweetest smile

1151
01:53:17,283 --> 01:53:20,047
For a whole year...
- You never spoke ?

1152
01:53:20,286 --> 01:53:26,555
When our eyes were saying so much
how could words dare to interfere ?

1153
01:53:28,827 --> 01:53:29,623
But...

1154
01:53:32,431 --> 01:53:35,229
l can shower her with gifts, can't l ?

1155
01:53:35,768 --> 01:53:41,070
So every week, l'd fall over myself
to give her my gift

1156
01:53:41,273 --> 01:53:42,740
And she...
- Would smile ?

1157
01:53:42,942 --> 01:53:43,567
And take it

1158
01:53:44,777 --> 01:53:49,908
And l'm sure that one day, in return for
all my gifts she would give me...

1159
01:53:50,115 --> 01:53:54,575
that one big gift l've been
waiting for.
- So did the gift arrive ?

1160
01:53:54,853 --> 01:53:56,081
Winter arrived

1161
01:53:58,958 --> 01:54:00,926
On the 2 1 st of December...

1162
01:54:01,961 --> 01:54:06,921
wrapped in a maroon shawl
and a warm smile...

1163
01:54:07,132 --> 01:54:09,259
she stepped into the bus.
Radiance on her face and in her hands...

1164
01:54:09,468 --> 01:54:15,100
a Golden Bakery box.
lnside that box...

1165
01:54:16,175 --> 01:54:22,944
were the world's most beautiful
heart shaped... you know...

1166
01:54:23,816 --> 01:54:26,284
heart-shaped pastries

1167
01:54:28,821 --> 01:54:32,450
And then
for the first time in a year...

1168
01:54:34,827 --> 01:54:37,955
she spoke her first words to me

1169
01:54:43,235 --> 01:54:44,293
Please...

1170
01:54:46,372 --> 01:54:50,308
would you distribute these pastries
to all the passengers

1171
01:54:50,843 --> 01:54:52,640
l just got engaged

1172
01:55:01,120 --> 01:55:02,960
Ei handsome
- Yeah?

1173
01:55:04,857 --> 01:55:06,154
What happened ?

1174
01:55:29,048 --> 01:55:30,174
She's calling you

1175
01:55:32,217 --> 01:55:33,013
Who is ?

1176
01:55:33,952 --> 01:55:37,353
Tonight's your night

1177
01:55:40,726 --> 01:55:46,187
Those pangs you feel in your heart
have pained me too

1178
01:55:47,900 --> 01:55:52,200
Why not drown our pains tonight?

1179
01:55:54,406 --> 01:55:55,031
Nice

1180
01:56:02,915 --> 01:56:09,718
Rare are those moments in life
when desire calls

1181
01:56:12,257 --> 01:56:16,557
Come into my arms,
or come and slit my throat

1182
01:56:28,273 --> 01:56:29,740
Oh forget it...

1183
01:56:30,442 --> 01:56:33,070
this give and take of hearts
takes a lot of heart...

1184
01:56:33,612 --> 01:56:39,244
and doing it so boldly for the world
to see... it's a woman's art you see

1185
01:56:40,119 --> 01:56:43,452
ln this winning and losing
of hearts what are men worth ?

1186
01:56:46,625 --> 01:56:55,761
<i>His ruthless gaze...</i>

1187
01:56:55,968 --> 01:56:58,937
<i>tore up the street...</i>

1188
01:56:59,705 --> 01:57:05,940
<i>took me apart</i>

1189
01:57:06,745 --> 01:57:11,114
<i>lt ran a razor's edge
down the willing side of my heart</i>

1190
01:57:48,821 --> 01:57:51,813
<i>TmG</i>

1191
01:57:53,659 --> 01:57:56,822
<i>l fall to restless pieces...</i>

1192
01:57:58,697 --> 01:58:03,498
<i>don't look at me that way</i>

1193
01:58:03,702 --> 01:58:13,668
<i>l fall to restless pieces,
don't look at me that way</i>

